---
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
import ImageCard from "../components/ImageCard.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PlayerList from "../components/PlayerList.svelte"
---

<Layout title="CraftNectar Minecraft Server">
  <div class="craftnectar-header">
    <video
      class="mb-6"
      width="100%"
      height="auto"
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      id="parkour"
    >
      <source src="/videos/parkour.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
    </video>
    <div class="video-overlay">
      <h1
        class="font-extrabold text-transparent text-6xl bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r m-b-0 from-yellow-400 to-amber-600"
      >
        CraftNectar
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 pt-0 pl-8">Vanilla 1.20.1 Server w/ Plugins</p>
      <p class="text-lg">
        CraftNectar is my 1.20.1 Paper server which houses a rather unique RPG experience for players to enjoy.

        Boasting custom items, GUI's, world generation, economy, minigames, and so much more - CraftNectar offers players endless hours of enjoyment. Here are just a few of
        the things the server has to offer players:
      </p>
      <ul class="px-8 list-disc">
        <li>Custom Generated Survival World</li>
        <li>Over 200 Custom Items w/ Unique Modifiers</li>
        <li>Around 20 pets with custom models/skills</li>
        <li>In-Game Economy</li>
        <li>Land-Claiming via GUI</li>
        <li>Custom server shop with custom GUI</li>
      </ul>
      <section>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-evenly -mx-1 lg:-mx-4">
          <PlayerList client:load/>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>



  <section>
    <div class="container my-12 mx-auto px-4 md:px-12">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-evenly -mx-1 lg:-mx-4">
        <ImageCard title="Custom Items" imageURI="items.png">
          <span
            >We develop our very own items for the server. Using MMO items we're
            able to Lock certian items behind level or attribute requirements.
            In true MMO fashion, weapons have a chance to spawn with unique
            modifiers.</span
          >
        </ImageCard>
        <ImageCard title="Furniture" imageURI="furniture.png">
          <span
            >
            Who needs furniture mods? Offered in the server resource pack, we have plenty of furniture available to make your house a home.
            </span
          >
        </ImageCard>
        <ImageCard
          title="Custom GUI's"
          imageURI="menu.png"
        >
          <span
            >Ugly default GUI's offer a poor user experience in my opinion. That's why I've went through great lenghts in order to provide our
            users with custom GUI's wherever possible - even creating my own where neccessary, such as the server main menu.</span
          >
        </ImageCard>
        <ImageCard title="Custom Pets" imageURI="pets.png">
          <span
            >Like cute little deadly pets? Enjoy flying giant dragons? Come on by, we've got tons of pets!</span
          >
        </ImageCard>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <p>A paragraph</p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  p {
    @apply p-4;
  }
  .feature {
    width: 100%;
    @apply pl-4;
  }
  .feature span {
    @apply pl-6;
  }
  .feature li {
    list-style: circle;
  }
  .feature a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    @apply text-pink-300;
  }
  .video-overlay {
    position: relative;
    top: 68px;
    color: #f1f1f1;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .craftnectar-header {
    width: 100%;
    position: relative;
  }
  #parkour {
    position: absolute;
    position: fixed;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: calc(100vh + 10%);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  video {
    filter: brightness(30%);
  }
</style>
